46. Write a PHP program to find the index of a specific value in an array
CODE:
<?php
$fruits = array("Apple", "Banana", "Cherry", "Mango");

// Value to search
$search = "Cherry";

// Find index
$index = array_search($search, $fruits);

if ($index !== false) {
    echo "'$search' found at index: $index";
} else {
    echo "'$search' not found in the array.";
}
?>
OUTPUT:
'Cherry' found at index: 2
